Alembic migrations for the calorie-bot Postgres schema.

Commands (run from repo root):

  uv run alembic upgrade head              # apply all pending migrations
  uv run alembic revision -m "add foo"     # create a new empty migration
  uv run alembic downgrade -1              # roll back one revision
  uv run alembic current                   # show current DB revision

The DATABASE_URL env var overrides alembic.ini's sqlalchemy.url. Inside
docker compose, the `migrate` service runs `alembic upgrade head` once on
startup before the app service boots.

Migrations are written as raw SQL via op.execute(...) -- we do not use
SQLAlchemy models. Keep the SQL idempotent-friendly where practical
(CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS, etc.).
